			>
			<DIV><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size=4>If you are going to go off on things to remove from the pvp servers, I do have a few suggestions myself.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size=4></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size=4>First off, remove the /who command or limit it somehow to within a certain distance from the person making the /who inquiry.&nbsp; If you can only tell who is in a given zone by sight&nbsp; or by tracking, then it 1) adds a little spice to the pvp hunting experience, 2) will remove the inhibition of seeing enemy players in a zone you want to hunt in, and 3) stymy griefing a bit because you cant tell if someone you are after has come back in your area.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size=4></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size=4>Yes this would give classes with tracking a small edge, ie rangers, druids, and bards, however, Sony could fiddle with the tracking difficulty when trying to track players.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size=4></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size=4>Discussing tracking, how about adding a particle effect, similar to the find ribbon, in the form of a trail of footprints, for a tracker to follow?</FONT></DIV>	
