		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Here is how you fix 'exploiting' of the bounty system.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Make it so the person who sets a bounty AND the person that makes the kill cannot trade the amount of the bounty (minus the fee) with that person.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Call it a double fine if you will.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>i.e.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Person 1 places a bounty on Person 2.</DIV>
<DIV>Person 3 kills person 2 and collects the bounty Person 1 placed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Person 1 and 3 cannot trade coin to person 2 in the amount of the bounty (keep a running total) if they do it goes poof (and reduces the running total of non-tradeable coin)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>further example.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Person 1 places a 5000pp bounty on person 2.</DIV>
<DIV>Person 3 kills person 2 and person 1 ok's the transfer of the 4500pp. (10% fee deducted)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Person 3 tries to trade 4500pp to person 2 but it goes poof because person 3 has a 'trade defict' &nbsp;to person 2.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>exploit fixed. next <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>	
