<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=6653#M6653">66</a> of 71
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 123 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><STRONG><U>Bounty System Summarize</U></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So far we got:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<UL>
<LI>Bounty system is very easy to exploit, so we need to recheck the rules</LI>
<LI>Player #1 make a bounty on Player #2</LI>
<LI>Name / Race / Lvl / Deity&nbsp;on Player #2 must appear at Bounty description (Race/Deity war Zek Servers)</LI>
<LI>Player #3 ask for acceptance of being the bounty hunter</LI>
<LI>Player can accept or reject player #3 in this case he accept</LI>
<LI>Player #1 will get substracted immediately the money chosed as bounty</LI>
<LI>The bounty description will be invisble on Bounty board</LI>
<LI>Player #2 will be informed (tell/motd/Bounty Window) that on his head is now a bounty, but not how much and who the hunter is</LI>
<LI>Player #3 will get a message in his NEW BOUNTY Window that he has a new "Adventure" to solve the next 7 Days</LI>
<LI>If Player #3 isnt able to kill / Find player #2 in the next 7 days Bounty Adventure is closed and the Reward will go back to his owner Player #1 with a message why he got the money. (I suggest to put the money into Bank directly instead to char in the case he is just himself in a PvP fight) </LI>
<LI>To Punish a&nbsp;failed Bounty hunt I suggest a 1 kill EXP death of player #3 without the chance of Rezz. ( like appearing full equip in SR without a corpse ) Exp death is like 1% per &lt;= 100 pp. (so for like 1000pp bounty Player #3 loose 10% percent exp)</LI>
<LI>If Player #3 find player #2 then there are 2 choices:</LI>
<LI>a) Player #2 kills Player #3 : then Player #3 will loose one Exp Death (depending on bounty like above)&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;appear at SR full equipped. Also Player #3 and Player #1 will close their active status&nbsp;Bounty Window. Player #2 receives 50 percent of the money the bounty would be on his bank and will get informed in his Bounty window about it</LI>
<LI>b) Player #3 kills Player #2 : then Player #3 will get his bounty in his bank and Bounty window will be updated for Player #1, #2 and #3. Player #2 will appear full equipped at SR and loose Exp depending how much the bounty was. (I suggest 1% per&nbsp; &lt;=100pp)</LI>
<LI>To avoid Player Camping with bounty system these rules should also be: You can&nbsp;<U>only</U> have&nbsp;one active and one passive bounty adventure in your Bounty window at same time. Active = you are player #1 or Player #3 in this case. Passive = you are Player #2 in this case.</LI>
<LI>Add: If Bounty adventure locks out before the 7 Days are over you are have 12 hours to wait before going active/passive again. (this will cancel exp griefing atleast for the next 12 hours) so its enough time to find a safe place</LI></UL>
<P>So imo the only exploitation can be now made through Player #2 who can wait till next week before log in again, or stay like 7 days in safezones like bazaar. BUT if you placed a bounty on someone you expect that he is a griefer and this would stopped him for griefing with this char (atleast) for the next seven days too... And the Char placing the bounty would receive his bounty back too, so only the hunter is the one loosing the time.</P>
<P>I hope I got all summarized / made the rule now. Feel free to add things.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
